<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Phlox</i> <i>covillei</i> is characteristically present in the herbaceous and subshrub layers with <i>Arenaria</i> <i>kingii</i>, <i>Astragalus</i> <i>kentrophyta</i>, <i>Astragalus</i> <i>purshii</i>, <i>Astragalus</i> <i>whitneyi</i>, <i>Draba</i> <i>oligosperma</i>, <i>Elymus</i> <i>elymoides</i>, <i>Ericameria</i> <i>discoidea</i>, <i>Ericameria</i> <i>parryi</i>, <i>Erigeron</i> <i>compositus</i>, <i>Erigeron</i> <i>pygmaeus</i>, <i>Eriogonum</i> <i>gracilipes</i>, <i>Eriogonum</i> <i>incanum</i>, <i>Eriogonum</i> <i>ovalifolium</i>, <i>Festuca</i> <i>brachyphylla</i>, <i>Festuca</i> <i>minutiflora</i>, <i>Ivesia</i> <i>muirii</i>, <i>Ivesia</i> <i>shockleyi</i>, <i>Linum</i> <i>lewisii</i>, <i>Penstemon</i> <i>davidsonii</i>, <i>Phacelia</i> <i>hastata</i>, <i>Phlox</i> <i>pulvinata</i>, <i>Poa</i> <i>glauca</i> ssp. <i>rupicola</i>, <i>Podistera</i> <i>nevadensis</i> and <i>Selaginella</i> <i>watsonii</i>. </div>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  Herbs < 40 cm; cover is open to intermittent. </div>
</div>

        
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Membership Rules</h4>
	<ul class="text">
		
		<li><i>Phlox covillei, Elymus elymoides, Festuca minutiflora</i>, and/or other low perennial, matted herbs occur characteristically in the herbaceous layer; plants typically < 25% absolute cover (Keeler-Wolf et al. 2003b).</li>
		
	</ul>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> Alpine fell-fields on windswept summits and ridges. Lag gravel covers the soil, and patterned ground features are common. Substrates can be granitic and metamorphic, including marble.  </div>
</div>

        
